Sime Darby to Conduct Biogas Trial on Eight Malaysian Estates, Dass Says

-- B y   C h o n g   P o o i   K o o n
-- 
2011-04-04T09:19:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-04/sime-darby-to-conduct-biogas-trial-on-eight-malaysian-estates-dass-says.html
Sime Darby Bhd. (SIME) , the world’s biggest
oil palm planter, will conduct a feasilibility over two years
into tapping its estates for biogas, Executive Vice President
Franki Anthony Dass told reporters in Kuala Lumpur today.  Some eight mills on Peninsular Malaysia will be involved in
the trial that will be conducted in partnership with  Tenaga
Nasional Bhd. (TNB)  and Mitsui & Co. Ltd., he said. If the green light
is given, the biogas power plants would each be able to generate
as much as 2 megawatts, Azman Mohd, Tenaga’s chief operating
officer told reporters.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chong Pooi Koon in Kuala Lumpur at 
 pchong17@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
